    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 102.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19,
                            1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I sent yesterday a telegram to Japan stating that Li Hung-chang had been
                        named plenipotentiary. His honors were restored to-day. He will hand over
                        his duties as viceroy. He will be here the 21st instant. Japan was asked to
                        name a place of meeting of plenipotentiaries. His credentials will be full
                        powers to conclude and to sign peace treaty.</p>
            </div>
